    <p class="govuk-body">
      Your device is now ready to be reset to factory settings. This will usually take between 40
      and 60 minutes.
    </p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      Enter recovery mode
    </h3>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      Open the Windows Start menu and select the power button. While holding down &lsquo;Shift&rsquo; select &lsquo;Restart&rsquo;.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">The device should restart to a blue recovery mode screen.</p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      If the above method is not successful, try pressing and holding the following keys while
      your device is booting:
    </p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Acer &ndash; F2.</li>
      <li>ASUS &ndash; F9.</li>
      <li>Dell &ndash; F8.</li>
      <li>Dynabook &ndash; 0 (zero).</li>
      <li>HP &ndash; F11.</li>
      <li>Lenovo &ndash; FN+F11 at the same time.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      Consult the manufacturer&rsquo;s guidance for specific instructions if the methods above do not work.
    </p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      Perform a factory reset
    </h3>

    <p class="govuk-body">From the recovery mode menu:</p>

    <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
      <li>select &lsquo;Troubleshoot&rsquo; and select &lsquo;Reset this PC&rsquo; &ndash; if you&rsquo;re asked where to reinstall Windows, select &lsquo;Local Reinstall&rsquo;</li>
      <li>select &lsquo;Remove everything&rsquo; &ndash; your screen may go blank for a short period after this</li>
      <li>when asked if you want to keep this PC set up for your workspace, select &lsquo;No&rsquo;</li>
      <li>select &lsquo;Clean the drive fully&rsquo; and select &lsquo;Reset&rsquo; when prompted</li>
    </ol>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      The device will now enter the reset process &ndash; this usually takes between 40 and 60 minutes.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      If you cannot complete these steps, the BIOS password process may not have been
      completed correctly. Revisit
      <%= govuk_link_to 'step 2 of this guide', devices_guide_to_resetting_windows_laptops_and_tablets_get_local_admin_and_bios_passwords_path %>,
      or
      <%= govuk_link_to 'contact us', support_ticket_path %>
      if you require additional support.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      The reset is complete when you see either the Windows setup screen or a black screen
      with white text asking if you wish to remove the TPM (Trusted Platform Module). This is up
      to your organisation&rsquo;s preferences and not part of our reset guidance.
    </p>

